leVictorian affair, of a nice, rough, tawny shade threaded with silver. Itreached up to my apple-red cheekbones and came down to my waistcoat,commingling on the way with my lateral yellow-gray locks. Special contactlenses not only gave another, dumbfounded, expression to my eyes, butsomehow changed their very shape from squarish leonine, to round Jovian.Only upon my return did I notice that the old tailor-made trousers, on meand in my bag, displayed my real name on the inside of the waistband.

